Program: Discovery
Title: Living Together - gannets
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrymt
Last Broadcast Date: 17 March 2004
Gannet colonies bear similarities to human congregations, so can they teach us anything? At a barren island just off the coast of Scotland is a huge gannet colony. Every year the birds arrive to turn the island into a 'bird city' in order to breed; and do so successfully with strict social rules, every year. Show less